job_description:
Why join us?

Our purpose is design for the good of humankind. It’s the ideal we strive toward each day in everything we do. Being a part of MillerKnoll means being a part of something larger than your work team, or even your brand. We are redefining modern for the 21st century. And our success allows MillerKnoll to support causes that align with our values, so we can build a more sustainable, equitable, and beautiful future for everyone.

GENERAL PURPOSE

The Operations Business Intelligence team is a new team at MillerKnoll created to support the specific strategic analytics needs of various Operations functions such as Quality, Distribution, Manufacturing, Logistics, Engineering, and Procurement. This is a cross-functional role which combines strategic and analytical capabilities with dedicated subject matter expertise sourced from Operations functions and data engineering capabilities. We work on opportunities which require the translation of business challenges into analytic solutions through data processing and analysis in order to draw insight from our data, improve business outcomes, and support decision making. The work includes creating data structures, dashboards, visualizations, and sustainable and automated solutions that empower analysis throughout the organization.

This role will:

Provide data driven insights and analytical support in solving strategic and operational problems by working with large data sets and translating into actionable insights, analytic dashboards, and/or reports that will influence business decisions.

Develop and maintain strong working relationships with internal customers and work closely with them to understand and anticipate needs and opportunities.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

Perform functions related to requirements definition, data analysis, data automation, visual analytics, and BI tool utilization. Provide ad-hoc/special project data analysis for business leaders, enabling them to achieve goals, drive decision making, impact new strategies and make improvements.

Develop business acumen within the Operations and Supply Chain functions.

Establish and maintain strong working relationships with Manufacturing, Logistics, and Supply Management teams, becoming the go-to resource for analytical support.

Build scalable data architecture and re-usable analytics assets for broader consumption within the organization. Seek opportunities to improve data collection, identify links among datasets, and drive global alignment.

Navigate within established technology environments to locate, validate, extract, and format the correct data for data analysis. Identify and define data assets that relate to critical business functions. Modify and run queries and standard reports from data tools and provide to users.

Ensure that processes and services are continuously monitored for data accuracy, reliability, integrity, and quality. Engage in process and quality improvement activities, including defining and maintaining data governance to optimize data quality and transparency.

Continuously study the entire Operations and BI professional fields, including market trends, research and best practices, to maintain the professional competence, knowledge, and skills necessary for the satisfactory performance of all assigned responsibilities.

May provide system configuration and administration for other critical systems that support Operations and Supply Chain.

Performs additional responsibilities as requested to achieve business objectives.

Additional Essential Functions

Performs additional responsibilities as requested to achieve business objectives.

QUALIFICATIONS

To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

Education/Experience

Education/Experience - Not Parsed

Bachelor's Degree in Business Intelligence, Data Analytics, Data Science, Database Systems, or relevant academic discipline preferred.

Minimum 5-7 years of professional analytics and technology experience.

5+ years of experience in report development, data science, business analytics, business intelligence, or comparable data engineering role, including data warehousing and business intelligence tools, techniques, and technology.

Licenses and Certifications

Alteryx Core Designer (preferred)..

Tableau Desktop Specialist (preferred)..

Skills and Abilities

Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills.

Experience with building front-end dashboards using Tableau required. Intermediate level ability desired.

Working knowledge of SQL to query large and complex data sets, test query results, and tune query performance required.

Working knowledge of ETL (Extract-Transform-Load) concepts for acquiring, cleansing, and combining diverse and disparate data sets preferred.

Intermediate-level experience with Alteryx preferred.

Working knowledge of a data analytics programming language such as Python, R and/or SAS preferred.

Ability to effectively communicate complex ideas regarding data analysis in an understandable, clear and concise manner.

Ability to explain complicated or technical information in a simple way to non-technical audiences

Sensitivity to clients' needs and ability to develop and maintain warm client relationships.

Curiosity and passion about data, visualization, and solving problems.

Creativity to determine the best solution for a real-world problem with quantitative data.

Additional Skills and Abilities

PHYSICAL DEMANDS

The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions

Must be able to perform all essential functions of the position with or without accommodations.

Who We Hire?

Simply put, we hire qualified applicants representing a wide range of backgrounds and abilities. MillerKnoll is comprised of people of all abilities, gender identities and expressions, ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, veterans from every branch of military service, and more. Here, you can bring your whole self to work. We’re committed to equal opportunity employment, including veterans and people with disabilities.

This organization participates in E-Verify Employment Eligibility Verification. In general, MillerKnoll positions are closed within 45 days and are open for applications for a minimum of 5 days. We encourage our prospective candidates to submit their application(s) expediently so as not to miss out on our opportunities. We frequently post new opportunities and encourage prospective candidates to check back often for new postings.

MillerKnoll complies with applicable disability laws and makes reasonable accommodations for applicants and employees with disabilities. If reasonable accommodation is needed to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and/or to receive other benefits and privileges of employment, please contact MillerKnoll Talent Acquisition at

careers_help@millerknoll.com

job_description:
When you join the team at Unum, you become part of an organization committed to helping you thrive.

Here, we work to provide the employee benefits and service solutions that enable employees at our client companies to thrive throughout life’s moments. And this starts with ensuring that every one of our team members enjoys opportunities to succeed both professionally and personally. To enable this, we provide:
• Award-winning culture
• Inclusion and diversity as a priority
• Performance Based Incentive Plans
• Competitive benefits package that includes: Health, Vision, Dental, Short & Long-Term Disability
• Generous PTO (including paid time to volunteer!)
• Up to 9.5% 401(k) employer contribution
• Mental health support
• Career advancement opportunities
• Student loan repayment options
• Tuition reimbursement
• Flexible work environments
• All the benefits listed above are subject to the terms of their individual Plans.

And that’s just the beginning…

With 10,000 employees helping more than 39 million people worldwide, every role at Unum is meaningful and impacts the lives of our customers. Whether you’re directly supporting a growing family, or developing online tools to help navigate a difficult loss, customers are counting on the combined talents of our entire team. Help us help others, and join Team Unum today!
General Summary:
We are seeking a creative, curious, and adaptable early-career analyst to join our People Analytics team. As a Business Intelligence Analyst I (the second level in a five-tier Business Intelligence career path), you will perform foundational data reporting, analysis, and insight generation, working in systems like Workday, Tableau, and ServiceNow. In this role, you will collaborate with fellow BIAs, HR Business Partners, HR leaders, and cross-functional teams to enable data-driven talent decisions within our People & Communications organization and across the enterprise.

Principal Duties and Responsibilities
• Conduct data profiling and analysis to evaluate data sources to determine the best source for business information
• Acquiring, transforming and translating data into actionable dashboards, reports, algorithms or datasets with minimal support from mentor and manager
• Performing statistical analysis and presenting findings to guide and advise leadership
• Collaborate with data engineers to perform data validation and testing activities as appropriate
• Continuously develop and build upon existing knowledge of the insurance industry
• Continuously develop and build upon existing knowledge of data stored in company databases
• Works directly with internal customers to refine requirements and validate output to ensure solutions will meet expectations

Job Specifications
• Bachelors Degree preferred, and/or equivalent experience
• 2+ years experience with demonstrated success at an Associate level in a data analytics related field
• Knowledge of analytics programming languages (SQL/R/Python)
• Experience with modern BI toolsets (Tableau, Alteryx, PowerBI, or equivalent)
• Understanding of data profiling, statistical analysis and data modeling concepts
• Comfortable extracting and leveraging data out of data warehouse, transactional databases, object stores & API based environments
• Demonstrated ability to translate business needs into technical solutions
• Ability to embrace change, adapt to the unexpected, and focus energies, people, and solutions on practical and positive results
• Demonstrated problem solving skills
• Strong communications skills
• Aptitude and drive to learn new technologies and analysis techniques
• Strong team player; able to work effectively within a team and more broadly with people from a variety of backgrounds and areas across the organization.
• Experience/certification in Workday a plus
• Experience with HR analytics or HR functional areas a plus

Colonial Life is headquartered in Columbia, SC, with over 40 field offices nationwide.

• *Overview:*The Pittsburgh Penguins seek a driven Business Intelligence Analyst Fellow passionate about data-driven decision-making for a 12-month program. The Fellow will contribute to key Business Intelligence and Analytics initiatives using data and technology and collaborate with other business operations stakeholders to analyze key business metrics. This fellowship position is a mix of analytical and operational responsibilities, will focus primarily on ticket sales and fan data-related initiatives to drive insights and identify revenue opportunities. In addition to the duties described above, the Business Intelligence Analyst Fellow will also participate in the Penguins’ exclusive Leadership Development Program. This program will provide regular opportunities for professional development, exposure to organizational leadership, and the ability to develop skills critical for the Fellow’s future career growth. A fundamental part of the program will include clearly defined goals between the Fellow and their Supervisor that will be tracked and measured for progress throughout the term of the program. Responsibilities: Use technical and statistical methods to develop key insights and processes to support decision making across different business units including ticket sales, CRM, sponsorship, marketing, and digital.
• Utilize Tableau to create executive level dashboards
• Analyze fan related data as it relates to demographics, psychographics, behavior and historical trends
• Develop and apply statistical models to business processes
• Help facilitate A/B testing implementation and analysis
• Develop fan facing surveys and analyze survey data
• Maintain complex datasets with a focus on automated solutions
• Perform ad-hoc analysis as needed

• Some experience in a consulting, analyst, or similar role preferred (internship or full-time position)
• Programming experience (SQL preferred, R/Python a plus)
• Familiarity with business intelligence platforms (e.g. Tableau, Power BI, Domo, Excel)
• Experience working in a data warehouse environment and/or with relational databases
• Strong presentation skills and the ability to effectively communicate findings from complex data analysis
• Strong work ethic and professional decorum

job_description:
Our employees are at the heart of what we do: helping people, businesses and society prosper in good times and be resilient in bad times.
When you join our team, you are bringing this purpose to life alongside a passionate community.

Feel empowered to learn and grow while being valued for who you are. At Intact, we commit to supporting you in reaching your goals with tools, opportunities, and flexibility. It's our promise to you.

Who We Are

At Intact Insurance Specialty Solutions, we are experts at what we do in protecting what makes businesses unique.

Our deep understanding of the specialty insurance market is the foundation for our customized solutions, backed by targeted risk control and claims services.

Our employees are passionate about providing insurance coverage that's aligned to our targeted customer groups.

Intact's Global Specialty Lines business spans across more than 20 verticals in four distinct markets: U.S., Canada, UK and Europe.
The following opportunity is for our U.S. team.

The opportunity

We currently have an opportunity for a Business Intelligence Analyst to join our Surety team based in our Southfield, MI office on a hybrid schedule.

This role is ideal for someone who enjoys working with data, wants to deepen their Power BI expertise, and cares about creating analytics that are not only accurate and performant, but also intuitive and well-designed.

You'll work on meaningful projects used by business leaders, learn modern BI best practices, and be supported by experienced teammates who care about quality, performance, thoughtful design, and continuous improvement.

Our Business Intelligence department operates at the forefront of reporting and analytics technology within a rapidly expanding global surety industry.

We invest heavily in modern platforms, strong architecture, and scalable solutions that set the standard for how data is modeled, governed, and delivered.
Some of the Business Intelligence Analyst responsibilities include but are not limited to:

Partner with business stakeholders to translate requirements into practical BI solutions.
Create clear, intuitive dashboards that balance business usability with technical rigor.
Identify and troubleshoot data quality or logic issues that impact reporting.
Design and maintain scalable Power BI data models that support enterprise reporting.
Apply strong UI/UX principles to ensure reports are visually consistent, accessible, and easy to navigate.
Build and optimize DAX measures, including time intelligence and more advanced calculations.
Develop Power Query transformations to stage, cleanse, and shape data efficiently.
Apply and help evolve governance standards (security, deployment pipelines, certified datasets).
Collaborate with other BI developers through reviews and shared best practices.

The expertise you bring

Bachelor's degree.
3–5 years of experience in business intelligence or analytics.
Strong hands-on Power BI experience (semantic modeling, DAX, Power Query).
Comfort working with SQL and enterprise data sources.
Experience supporting production BI content with a focus on reliability and performance.
Ability to communicate trade-offs, assumptions, and definitions clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences.

Our salary ranges are determined by many factors including location, role, experience and skillset of the candidate.

The following ranges displayed reflect the target base salary for new hires; however, your recruiter will provide more specific compensation details during the hiring process.
The typical base salary range for this position is:
$78,000 - $109,000 based on the factors aforementioned. For candidates located in San Francisco, CA; Washington DC; our Massachusetts based offices and the New York City metro area, the base salary range is $98,000 - $114,000.

In addition to base salary, full time Intact employees are also eligible for bonus potential and a full range of benefits to include but not limited to:

Comprehensive medical, dental and vision insurance with no waiting period
Competitive paid time off programs
401(k) savings and annual contributions of up to 12% of annual salary
Mental health support programs, life and disability insurance, paid parental leave and a variety of additional voluntary benefits

This position will remain posted until a final candidate is selected. Once the role is filled, this job posting will be removed.

Why choose Intact

We live our Values:

We are committed to acting with the highest of ethical standards through our five core values: integrity, respect, customer driven, excellence and social responsibility.

Our commitment to Diversity:

Founded in our values, we see diversity as a strength and aspire to create an environment where everyone can be themselves, grow and succeed.
Together, we will stand up for what's right to build an inclusive society.

Manage your Time:
What you accomplish matters more than hours in the office. We are committed to creating a positive and supportive environment in which you perform your best. Our Time-Off and Flexible Work Arrangement options help foster a healthy work-life balance.

Check out our Glassdoor reviews to see why people love working for Intact

Our promise to you

Our Values are foundational to our success at Intact.

You'll make a difference every day when you live our Values, do your best work, are open to change, and invest in yourself.
In return, we promise you support, opportunities, and performance-led financial rewards in a flexible work environment where you can:

Shape the future:
Help us lead an insurance transformation to better protect people, businesses and society.

Win as a team:

Collaborate with inspiring people to do your best work every day and together, stand up for what is right.

Grow with us:
Refresh and reinvent your skills, learn from our diverse teams, lift others up, and grow.

Our employees are passionate about providing insurance coverage that's aligned to our targeted customer groups. Today, we help protect over a dozen industries with tailored coverages and services.

This full-time Analyst, Data Visualization and Business Intelligence role is based on-site at the Royal Caribbean Miami 1050 Building and reports to the Sr Manager, Business Intelligence. job_description:
JLL empowers you to shape a brighter way.

Our people at JLL are shaping the future of real estate for a better world by combining world class services, advisory and technology for our clients. What this job involves:

This position serves as the critical link between data engineering capabilities and business outcomes within the Global Corporate Sustainability organization, requiring a unique blend of technical expertise and business acumen to transform sustainability data into actionable insights. You will own end-to-end data solutions for assigned GCS program areas including building performance, energy management, leasing assessment, and guidelines and standards from collection and modeling to storage and analytics. This role contributes to JLL's business objectives by establishing data governance standards, developing scalable analytics solutions, and fostering a data-driven culture that drives measurable business impact across GCS programs and regions.

• Serve as primary data point of contact for assigned GCS programs and regions while collaborating with program SMEs to prioritize objectives

job_title: Project Manager – Business Intelligence & Analytics – 1898 & Co.
job_description:
Description

Project Manager – Business Intelligence & Analytics – 1898 & Co.

Description

At 1898 & Co., a division of Burns & McDonnell, we are helping organizations make smarter decisions through data. Our Business Intelligence & Analytics (BI&A) team partners with clients to deliver digital transformation and enterprise data solutions that enable improved performance, visibility, and innovation. We bring together a team of experts in data engineering, analytics, and project management to support clients in developing scalable, insight-driven systems.

We are seeking a Project Manager within our Business Intelligence & Analytics business line who will lead a variety of digital transformation projects focused on data solutions. This individual will manage all phases of project delivery, from planning and estimation to execution and reporting, ensuring high-quality outcomes that meet client objectives. The role requires strong leadership, project execution, and collaboration capabilities, along with the ability to deliver results on time and within budget.

What You’ll Do

Business Development
• Identify and pursue new sales opportunities with clients to expand the BI&A business line.
• Lead proposal development and submission, including project estimation, planning, and scheduling.
• Establish critical project objectives and key performance indicators with clients.
• Lead contract preparation and negotiation in collaboration with internal teams and clients.
• Develop and maintain long-term relationships with client stakeholders, acting as a trusted partner in their data and analytics journey.

Project Execution
• Lead program estimation, planning, and budgeting activities, maintaining accountability for project execution and delivery.
• Adopt, implement, and adjust leading project delivery methodologies, including both Waterfall and Agile approaches.
• Manage full project lifecycles, ensuring alignment with client goals and adherence to schedule, budget, and quality expectations.
• Track and report overall project status, milestones, deliverables, and financial performance metrics.
• Create and deliver detailed project status reports and lead regular stakeholder meetings covering schedule, risks, issues, budget, and resource allocation.
• Supervise and coordinate all project resources, including internal 1898 & Co. teams, client personnel, and third-party vendors.
• Ensure project deliverables meet quality standards and contractual obligations.
• Support and oversee project deliverables assigned to both onshore and offshore teams, ensuring alignment with project objectives.
• Conduct quality assurance reviews of all deliverables to verify compliance with standards and best practices.
• Ensure adherence to company safety policies and quality standards throughout all project activities.
• Serve as the central point of contact for project interdependencies, ensuring seamless coordination between internal and external stakeholders.
• Utilize project management experience to influence project execution processes and quality assurance/quality control protocols.

Leadership & Mentorship
• Provide leadership and direction to multidisciplinary project teams, fostering collaboration and accountability.
• Mentor and develop team members by sharing knowledge and best practices related to project management, analytics, and digital transformation.
• Promote a culture of teamwork, customer commitment, and continuous improvement within the BI&A group.
• Champion innovation in project delivery and encourage adoption of new tools and methodologies that enhance client outcomes.
• Support staff development through coaching and professional growth opportunities.

Technical Responsibilities
• Lead and oversee the business process design phase to capture application requirements, including functional, technical, integration, and security needs.
• Validate that application requirements align with business processes, project scope, and strategic goals.
• Collaborate with staff managers to identify and develop training and performance support materials for project rollouts.
• Provide technical and strategic guidance on digital transformation initiatives involving data management, analytics, software engineering, and AI applications.
• Ensure project solutions align with business processes, data governance standards, and organizational objectives. Perform other duties as assigned.

Qualifications
• Bachelor Degree in engineering, business, computer science or related field from an accredited program and 5 years of relevant experience Required
• Knowledge in project management, techniques, and procedures.
• Excellent computer skills and proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook, PowerPoint).
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills and strong organizational skills.
• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, and attention to detail.
• Experience leading technical aspects of consulting engagements in regards statistical analysis, data wrangling and cleansing, application of analytics processing engines, or commercial analytics tooling.
• Experience on consulting projects, client operations, or executing program management within the critical infrastructure industry.
• Understanding of general business and financial principles.
• Experience with communicating across business segments to understand project objectives.

job_title: Digital & IT Senior Analyst - Website Optimization and Compliance
job_description:
Position Summary

The position is for a Product Owner overseeing optimization, performance, and compliance across Parker's websites. The role is responsible for driving measurable improvements in key performance indicators, including Apdex and Lighthouse scores, and ensuring ongoing adherence to applicable web standards and regulatory requirements. The Product Owner sets and executes Parker-Hannifin's organic search strategy across traditional search engines and AI-driven answer ecosystems. In partnership with the Search Engine Marketing Manager, this role designs data-driven plans that optimize for AI results (AEO/GEO) through both content and technical tactics. The specialist ensures Parker's websites achieve top SERP visibility while elevating digital customer experience (CX) through measurable performance improvements and content quality standards.

Responsibilities Primary Responsibilities:
Strategy & Governance
Lead advanced SEO strategies optimized for Generative Search (GEO) and Answer Engines (AEO) to grow qualified acquisition and brand visibility. Develop and maintain strategic plans detailing how Parker content surfaces in SERPs, LLM-driven assistants, and AI answer engines via structured data and conversational content. Define KPIs and measurement frameworks for SEO, AEO, and GEO; establish standards for content quality and premier CX on Parker websites. Manage the compliance guidance and recommendations across Parker websites through implementation and maintenance of a consent management platform. Technical & On-Page Optimization Implement and refine schema markup, entity-based SEO, and structured data to increase visibility in AI-powered interfaces and rich results. Drive site audits and improvements (crawlability, indexation, Core Web Vitals, Apdex score, internal linking, canonicalization, sitemaps, robots directives, hreflang). Design intent-driven content experiences that surface in featured snippets, AI-generated summaries, and conversational search results. Cross-Functional Collaboration Partner with Content, UX, Product, Engineering, and Digital Marketing teams to ensure experiences are optimized for traditional and AI search ecosystems. Translate business needs into technical requirements; coordinate implementation with web and development teams. Performance Management & Reporting
Manage, monitor, and improve website performance; build dashboards and recurring reports across SEO/AEO/GEO. Analyze results and convert insights into actionable recommendations for product and content teams. Educate stakeholders on emerging search behaviors and the impact of generative AI; proactively evolve strategies. Qualifications

job_title: Artificial Intelligence and Data Functional Engagement Manager
job_description:
Artificial Intelligence and Data Functional Engagement Manager

Company:
The Boeing Company

The Boeing Company is currently seeking an Artificial Intelligence and Data Functional Engagement Manager to join the team in Seattle, WA; Chicago, IL; Everett, WA; North Charleston, SC; Ridley Park, PA; Plano, TX; Pleasanton, CA; Renton, WA; Berkeley, MO; Mesa, AZ; Arlington, VA, El Segundo, CA or Long Beach, CA.

Enterprise AI and Data Analytics (EAI&D) is looking for an Engagement Manager who will specifically engage with our Boeing Functions on all Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data, Architecture, Software Development and Automation Products.

The role will focus on understanding the demand and opportunity for products with the functions, translating that into strategies, backlogs, and priorities for the Product and Delivery teams who develop the solutions, and applying Program Management best practices to ensure delivery on commitments and clear updates on status. The role will also partner with Information Technology (IT) Chief Information Officers (CIOs) and business partners on successful releases and adoption of solutions.

This individual will lead executive Stakeholder communications & management for both Boeing Functional Execs & Information Digital Technology & Security (IDT&S) CIO Teams.

You will be responsible for coordinating and partnering with our IT functional CIOs and Business Partners for a comprehensive IT strategy for the functions.

Position Responsibilities:
• Drive how Data, Analytics, AI & Automation can enable the business and create meaningful impact
• Own and drive the AI Strategy with our Boeing Functions and partner with peer leaders who have the same role for our Boeing businesses
• Build, own and maintain healthy analytics portfolio that maximizes business value & enables strategic priorities through a partner with the organization's product and delivery teams
• Hold EAI&D Product Family and Delivery teams accountable to deliver committed Analytics AI solutions by applying Program and Project Management best practices as well as establish and track Analytics Value & Communicate Success Stories
• Coordinate between EAI&D & Functions including Supply Chain, Manufacturing and Quality, Engineering, Human Resources (HR), Finance and others
• Drive the development of business functional Data, Analytics, AI and Automation roadmaps for the functions through a partnership with the product and delivery teams for a full picture of capabilities to the functions

BasicQualifications (Required Skills/Experience):
• Bachelor's degree or higher
• 10+ years of experience collaborating with senior management and/or executive leadership
• 5+ years of experience working as an executive or senior manager
• 5+ years of experience developing communication plans including stakeholder analysis, communication strategies, and key message development
• 5+ years of experience creating and analyzing data to identify data trends and communicate a story to depict findings
• 5+ years of experience in developing solutions to a wide range of complex technical problems, requiring ingenuity and innovation
• Experience as a self-starter with strong written and oral communication skills, and a focus on translating technically complex issues into simple, easy to understand concepts

Preferred Qualifications (Desired Skills/Experience):
• Master's degree or higher
